'''AgBiotechNet''' is a searchable [[online database]] of [[scientific literature]] on topics related to [[agricultural biotechnology]]. Its target audience consists of biotechnology researchers and policy makers. Though some features on the site are available for free, others can only be accessed by paid subscribers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.scidev.net/global/link/agbiotechnet.html |title=AgBiotechNet |website=SciDev |language=en |access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref> First launched in January 1999,<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Nicholson |first=David |date=January 2001 |title=New business models: AgBiotechNet™, a case study |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1087/09531510125100287 |journal=Learned Publishing |language=en |volume=14 |issue=1 |pages=55–59 |doi=10.1087/09531510125100287 |issn=0953-1513}}</ref> AgBiotechNet is run by the [[Centre for Agriculture and Bioscience International]] (also known as CABI), which founded it along with [[Michigan State University]]'s Agricultural Biotechnology Support Project.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Hemming |first=David |date=Winter 2004 |title=Staying on Top of Agbiotech -- An International Perspective |url=http://www.istl.org/04-winter/article2.html |journal=Issues in Science and Technology Librarianship |doi=10.5062/f4p26w2x}}</ref>
